77c31875-0d55-4cbb-a06b-b85708fdd145	<p>UAE-based tech ecosystem company Yango Group has introduced <strong>Yango Ventures</strong>, a $20 million corporate venture fund aimed at fueling the growth of innovative startups across key global markets. The fund will provide capital and strategic support to promising early-stage companies in LATAM, Sub-Saharan Africa, MENAP, and other high-potential regions.</p><p>Yango Ventures will focus on startups from <strong>Seed to Series B</strong> that are transforming the <strong>O2O (Online-to-Offline), B2B SaaS, and fintech</strong> sectors. In addition to financial investment, the fund will offer entrepreneurs access to Yango Group’s extensive expertise, global network, and market insights to help scale their businesses and create lasting economic impact.</p><p><em>"We’re not just investing in technology—we’re investing in people and communities. Yango Ventures is an extension of our commitment to empowering entrepreneurs with the tools, knowledge, and connections they need to succeed,"</em> said <strong>Daniil Shuleyko, CEO of Yango Group</strong>. <em>"By fostering innovation in high-growth regions, we aim to support local talent and drive sustainable business expansion that benefits entire economies."</em></p><p>While initially launching with a $20 million fund, Yango Ventures is structured for scalability, with plans to expand its investment capacity in response to the evolving needs of the startup ecosystem. The fund’s goal is to <strong>promote digital transformation</strong> and support businesses that are shaping the future of fintech, mobility, entertainment, AI, and other technology-driven industries.</p><p>Backing Yango Ventures is a team of experienced professionals with a proven track record of <strong>scaling B2B SaaS and B2C technology platforms</strong> across various industries. Their expertise in building and expanding businesses globally will provide founders with critical mentorship, strategic insights, and operational guidance.</p><p>Yango Ventures is part of Yango Group’s broader initiative to drive digital transformation and <strong>strengthen local innovation ecosystems</strong>. In addition to funding startups, the company actively supports entrepreneurial communities through <strong>networking events, educational partnerships, and skill-building initiatives</strong> designed to equip future innovators with practical knowledge and industry connections.</p><p>With this latest initiative, Yango Group reaffirms its commitment to <strong>harnessing technology for global progress</strong>, helping startups turn groundbreaking ideas into scalable, impactful solutions.</p>	{"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "UAE-based tech ecosystem company Yango Group has introduced ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Yango Ventures", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": ", a $20 million corporate venture fund aimed at fueling the growth of innovative startups across key global markets. The fund will provide capital and strategic support to promising early-stage companies in LATAM, Sub-Saharan Africa, MENAP, and other high-potential regions.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "Yango Ventures will focus on startups from ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "Seed to Series B", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " that are transforming the ", "type": "text"}, {"text": "O2O (Online-to-Offline), B2B SaaS, and fintech", "type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"text": " sectors. In addition to financial investment, the fund will offer entrepreneurs access to Yango Group’s extensive expertise, global network, and market insights to help scale their businesses and create lasting economic impact.", "type": "text"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"text": "\\"We’re not just investing in technology—we’re investing in people and communities. Yango Ventures is an extension of our commitment to empow